This error occurs when you try to cast a Double object to a Long object, which is not possible. Since Double is a subclass of Number and Long is also a subclass of Number, the two classes are not compatible for casting. 

To fix this issue, you can either change the variable type to Double or use appropriate casting. For example, you can use Math.round() to convert a double value to a long value:

```
Double value = 5.5;
Long roundedValue = Math.round(value);
```

Alternatively, you can use Double.valueOf() to create a Double object instead of Long.parseLong():

```
Double value = 5.5;
Long longValue = Double.valueOf(value).longValue();
```

It's important to ensure that you use the appropriate casting when working with different data types.

